text: The International Commerce Centre is the tallest building in Hong Kong. The building was finished in 2009 and has a height of 1,588 feet. It has 118 floors.CTBUH: International Commerce Centre Skyscraperpage : ICC Inside the top floors of the building is a hotel for people to stay in. ==References== Category:Skyscrapers in China Category:Buildings and structures in Hong Kong
title: International Commerce Centre
